In England, in the seven days to 21 February, there were 65,882 new confirmed cases (117.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 February, there were 75,334 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 13% (9,452 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 February is 3,646,745 (6,478.8 cases per 100,000 population).
